TY  - JOUR
AU  - Tédongap, Roméo
T1  - Consumption Volatility and the Cross-Section of Stock Returns*
PY  - 2015
Y1  - 2015/03/01
DO  - 10.1093/rof/rft058
JO  - Review of Finance
JA  - Rev Financ
VL  - 19
IS  - 1
SP  - 367
EP  - 405
SN  - 1572-3097
AB  - I derive and test multi-horizon implications of a consumption-based equilibrium model featuring fluctuating expected growth and volatility. My setup allows consumption dynamics to be estimated jointly with covariance risk prices in a single-stage generalized method of moment, and then inferences from asset pricing tests reflect uncertainty coming from factor estimation. I show that changes in consumption volatility are the key driver for explaining major asset pricing anomalies across risk horizons, while other factors play no or a secondary role. Value stocks and past long-term losers pay higher average returns mainly because they covary more negatively with these changes than what other stocks do.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rof/rft058
ER  - 



