TY  - JOUR
AU  - Andersen, Torben G.
AU  - Bondarenko, Oleg
T1  - Assessing Measures of Order Flow Toxicity and Early Warning Signals for Market Turbulence*
PY  - 2015
Y1  - 2015/03/01
DO  - 10.1093/rof/rfu041
JO  - Review of Finance
JA  - Rev Financ
VL  - 19
IS  - 1
SP  - 1
EP  - 54
SN  - 1572-3097
AB  - Following the “flash crash” on May 6, 2010, warning signals for impending market stress have been in high demand, yet only the VPIN metric of Easley, López de Prado, and O’Hara (ELO) has claimed success. In addition, ELO find the metric useful in predicting short-term volatility. VPIN involves decomposing volume into active buys and sells. We utilize quotes and trade data to construct an accurate trade classification measure for E-mini S&amp;P 500 futures. Against this benchmark, the ELO Bulk Volume Classification (BVC) scheme is inferior to a standard tick rule. Moreover, VPIN predicts volatility solely because increasing volatility induces systematic classification errors in the BVC procedure. We conclude that VPIN is unsuitable for capturing order flow toxicity or signaling ensuing market turbulence.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rof/rfu041
ER  - 



